    • getMatchboxEngine

      public MatchboxEngine getMatchboxEngine(@Nullable String canonical, @Nullable CliContext cliContext, boolean create, boolean reload) throws MatchboxEngineCreationException
      Returns a Matchbox engine for the specified canonical with cliClontext parameters. It is synchronized and waits for the 'initialized' flag.
      Parameters:
      canonical - URL to validate
      cliContext - cliContext parameters
      create - if true, create a new engine
      reload - if true, reload the engine
      Returns:
      a Matchbox engine.
      Throws:
      MatchboxEngineCreationException - if the engine cannot be created.

    • getMatchboxEngineNotSynchronized

      public MatchboxEngine getMatchboxEngineNotSynchronized(@Nullable String canonical, @Nullable CliContext cliContext, boolean create, boolean reload) throws MatchboxEngineCreationException
      Returns a Matchbox engine for the specified canonical with cliClontext parameters. This method is not synchronized and does not wait for the 'initialized' flag. It should be used only for internal calls from the IG Provider load-all method.
      Parameters:
      canonical - URL to validate
      cliContext - cliContext parameters
      create - if true, create a new engine
      reload - if true, reload the engine
      Returns:
      a Matchbox engine.
      Throws:
      MatchboxEngineCreationException - if the engine cannot be created.
